SIMPLE: looker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Looker
<hw>Look"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
looks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who is physically very attractive,
especially a beautiful woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Looker-on</b></col>, <cd>a spectator; an onlooker; one
that looks on, but has no agency or part in an affair.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Did not this fatal war affront thy coast,⟦br⟧
Yet sattest thou an idle <qex>looker-on</qex> ?</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Looking</ent>⟦br⟧
